'''''Star Wars: The Force Unleashed''''' was a planned [[Star Wars comic books|webstrip]] tie-in to [[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed|''The Force Unleashed'']] series, focusing on [[Shaak Ti/Legends|Shaak Ti]]. Along with ''[[Rookies: Day Long Remembered]]'', it was originally announced as being available to all on [[StarWars.com]], not just [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] subscribers.<ref>{{WordPress|subdomain=starwarsblog|url=2007/05/27/webstrip-chatter-at-celebration-iv/#more-57|name=Celebration IV|text=Webstrip Chatter|archivedate=20230427013915}}</ref> It was later revealed that it would only be available to Hyperspace subscribers, after all.<ref name="SWArchive-Hyperspace 2008: A Taste of What's to Come">{{SWArchive|url=hyperspace/about/news/news20080116.html|text=Hyperspace 2008: A Taste of What's to Come}}</ref> Hyperspace was shut down in [[2011]].<ref name="Hyperspace 2011">{{SWArchive|url=fans/news/hyperspace2010/index.html|text=Last Chance to Order the 2010 Hyperspace Member Kit!}}</ref> However, this webstrip was never published. As all other ''Star Wars: The Force Unleashed'' merchandise has long since been released, it is most likely that it was canceled.

